ing aspects of human interaction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  ainsult, offense, humor, audience, abuse, enmity, disdain, human interaction, martial, poet, henry ford, cicero, eminem, shakespeare, monty python, congress, rhetoric, communication, invective, nonfiction, language, falstaff, taunt, religion, shame, civility, hierarchies, class, power, authority, aesthetics, philosophy, satire, irony, politics, linguistics, lexicology, literature, anthropology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022611477440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226114798423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226114798/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles